{"id":167361,"name":"Custom Scrollbars in Firefox 63/64+","description":"Based on:\r\n\r\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/scrollbar-width\">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/scrollbar-width</a>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/scrollbar-color\">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/scrollbar-color</a></ul>","user":{"id":639306,"name":"krystian3w","email":"redacted","paypal_email":null,"homepage":null,"about":null,"license":"ccby"},"updated":"2020-07-20T08:58:35.000Z","weekly_install_count":0,"total_install_count":111,"rating":null,"after_screenshot_name":"https://userstyles.org/style_screenshots/167361_after.jpeg?r=1598601965","obsoleting_style_id":null,"obsoleting_style_name":null,"obsolete":0,"admin_delete_reason_id":null,"obsoletion_message":null,"screenshots":null,"license":"ccby","created":"2018-12-31T00:15:31.000Z","category":"global","raw_subcategory":null,"subcategory":null,"additional_info":"<b>*</b>On macOS, you need to set the <b>General</b> > <b>Show scroll bars setting</b> in <b>System Preferences</b> to \"<b>Always</b>\" for this property to have any effect.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>For version 63 only<b>: \r\n\r\nthis feature is behind the:\r\n\r\n<ul><li><code>layout.css.scrollbar-colors.enabled</code> \r\n<li><code>layout.css.scrollbar-width.enabled</code> </ul>\r\n\r\npreference (needs to be set to true). To change preferences in Firefox, visit <u>about:config</u>.","style_tags":[],"css":"@-moz-document regexp(\"^(https?|moz-extension|ftp)\\:\\/\\/.*$\") {\r\n\r\n    :root {\r\n        scrollbar-face-color: /*[[face-color]]*/ !important; \r\n        scrollbar-track-color: /*[[track-color]]*/ !important; \r\n  \r\n        scrollbar-color: /*[[face-color]]*/ /*[[track-color]]*/ !important;\r\n  \r\n        scrollbar-width: /*[[s-width]]*/ !important;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    select:not([multiple]), select:not([size]) {\r\n       scrollbar-width: auto